description:
Godland is written by Joe Casey and illustrated by Tom Scioli and published by Image Comics.

The series was conceived as both a homage to and a revival of the Cosmic Superhero Epic as told by many great comic writers of the 70s like Steve Engelhart, Jim Starlin and Jack Kirby.

The series centres on Adam Archer, an astronaut who is the sole survivor of an ill-fated journey to Mars. Adam Archer meets the alien entities known as the Cosmic Fetus Collective, who transform him into a cosmic being and instruct him in the uses of his new powers. Archer is sent back to Earth as the first human to be touched by universal enlightenment.
